    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="783"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d783">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/379: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 23, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>312. Nanking’s 937, November 20, 9 a.m., repeated to you by Shanghai.</p>
                <p>Ambassador Johnson has now notified the Department of his departure on November
                    23 from Nanking. However, as the Consulate General in Shanghai has presumably,
                    in pursuance of Nanking’s instructions, notified the Japanese authorities at
                    Shanghai of the Ambassador’s departure, the Department does not consider it
                    necessary that notification also be made by you to the Japanese Foreign Office
                    unless similar notification is being made by your principally interested
                    colleagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
